Document: PhysicsShapeQueryParameters2D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsshapequeryparameters2d.rst
Summary: Defines parameters for physics shape queries in 2D.

Inherits: Resource < Object

This class holds parameters for physics shape queries in 2D. It's used to configure how a shape should be queried against the physics world, for example, when performing raycasts or shape casts.

Key properties include:
* shape (Shape2D): The shape resource to use for the query.
* transform (Transform2D): The transform of the shape in the physics world.
* collision_mask (int): The collision layers the query should check against. Defaults to 4294967295 (all layers).
* exclude (Array[RID]): An array of RIDs to exclude from the query results.
* exclude_bodies (Array[NodePath]): An array of NodePaths to bodies to exclude from the query results.
* exclude_rid (RID): A single RID to exclude from the query results.
* space (RID): The physics space RID to query against. If empty, the default space is used.
* motion (Vector2): The motion vector to consider for the query. Useful for detecting collisions along a path.
* up_direction (Vector2): The up direction vector for queries that use it, like shape casts.
* collide_with_bodies (bool): Whether to collide with physics bodies. Defaults to true.
* collide_with_areas (bool): Whether to collide with physics areas. Defaults to false.
* hit_from_inside (bool): If true, shapes that are fully inside the queried shape will also be returned. Defaults to false.
* report_individual_hits (bool): If true, all individual shapes that collide will be reported. If false, only the first collision is reported. Defaults to false.
