Document: PhysicsShapeQueryParameters2D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsshapequeryparameters2d.rst
Summary: Configures parameters for PhysicsDirectSpaceState2D methods related to shape queries.

PhysicsShapeQueryParameters2D is used to configure the parameters for PhysicsDirectSpaceState2D's methods, allowing you to specify properties like the shape, collision mask, and other settings for physics queries in 2D.
---CHUNK---
Document: PhysicsShapeQueryParameters2D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsshapequeryparameters2d.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for a 2D physics shape query.

Properties:
* collide_with_areas (bool): If true, the query will collide with PhysicsArea2D nodes. Default: false.
* collide_with_bodies (bool): If true, the query will collide with PhysicsBody2D nodes. Default: true.
* collision_mask (int): The collision layers the query will check against. Default: 4294967295.
* exclude (Array[RID]): An array of RIDs to exclude from the query results. Default: [].
* margin (float): The margin to use for the shape query. Default: 0.0.
* motion (Vector2): The motion vector to use for the shape query. Default: Vector2(0, 0).
* shape (Resource): The shape resource to use for the query.
* shape_rid (RID): The RID of the shape resource to use for the query. Default: RID().
* transform (Transform2D): The transform to use for the shape query. Default: Transform2D(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0).
---CHUNK---
Document: PhysicsShapeQueryParameters2D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsshapequeryparameters2d.rst
Summary: Defines the properties for physics shape queries in 2D, including collision settings, masks, exclusions, and shape/transform data.

Property Descriptions
Property: collide_with_areas
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, the query will take Area2D s into account.
Set Method: set_collide_with_areas(value: bool)
Get Method: is_collide_with_areas_enabled()

Property: collide_with_bodies
Type: bool
Default: true
Description: If true, the query will take PhysicsBody2D s into account.
Set Method: set_collide_with_bodies(value: bool)
Get Method: is_collide_with_bodies_enabled()

Property: collision_mask
Type: int
Default: 4294967295
Description: The physics layers the query will detect (as a bitmask). By default, all collision layers are detected. See Collision layers and masks in the documentation for more information.
Set Method: set_collision_mask(value: int)
Get Method: get_collision_mask()

Property: exclude
Type: Array[RID]
Default: []
Description: The list of object RIDs that will be excluded from collisions. Use CollisionObject2D.get_rid() to get the RID associated with a CollisionObject2D-derived node.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. To update the value you need to modify the returned array, and then assign it to the property again.
Set Method: set_exclude(value: Array[RID])
Get Method: get_exclude()

Property: margin
Type: float
Default: 0.0
Description: The collision margin for the shape.
Set Method: set_margin(value: float)
Get Method: get_margin()

Property: motion
Type: Vector2
Default: Vector2(0, 0)
Description: The motion of the shape being queried for.
Set Method: set_motion(value: Vector2)
Get Method: get_motion()

Property: shape
Type: Resource
Description: The Shape2D that will be used for collision/intersection queries. This stores the actual reference which avoids the shape to be released while being used for queries, so always prefer using this over shape_rid.
Set Method: set_shape(value: Resource)
Get Method: get_shape()

Property: shape_rid
Type: RID
Default: RID()
Description: The queried shape's RID that will be used for collision/intersection queries. Use this over shape if you want to optimize for performance using the Servers API.
Set Method: set_shape_rid(value: RID)
Get Method: get_shape_rid()

GDScript:
var shape_rid = PhysicsServer2D.circle_shape_create()
var radius = 64
PhysicsServer2D.shape_set_data(shape_rid, radius)

var params = PhysicsShapeQueryParameters2D.new()
params.shape_rid = shape_rid

# Execute physics queries here...

# Release the shape when done with physics queries.
PhysicsServer2D.free_rid(shape_rid)

C#:
RID shapeRid = PhysicsServer2D.CircleShapeCreate();
int radius = 64;
PhysicsServer2D.ShapeSetData(shapeRid, radius);

var params = new PhysicsShapeQueryParameters2D();
params.ShapeRid = shapeRid;

// Execute physics queries here...

// Release the shape when done with physics queries.
PhysicsServer2D.FreeRid(shapeRid);

Property: transform
Type: Transform2D
Default: Transform2D(1, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0)
Description: The queried shape's transform matrix.
Set Method: set_transform(value: Transform2D)
Get Method: get_transform()